section.text:

Section 23 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (
  15 U.S.C. 78w
) is amended by adding at the end the following:

clause.text:
consistent with the requirements of 
                    section 3(f) (
                      15 U.S.C. 78c(f)
                    ), 
                    section 2(b) of the Securities Act of 1933 (
                      15 U.S.C. 77b(b)
                    ), 
                    section 202(c) of the Investment Advisers Act of 1940 (
                      15 U.S.C. 80b–2(c)
                    ), and 
                    section 2(c) of the Investment Company Act of 1940 (
                      15 U.S.C. 80a–2(c)
                    ), consider whether the rulemaking will promote efficiency, competition, and capital formation;

a regulation issued in accordance with the formal rulemaking provisions of section 556
                   or 
                    557 of title 5, United States Code;
